It was my honor to do the cover for @curbsideokc’s September issue, which is out now and contains a FREE ZOO TICKET! Go get a copy!! The Curbside Chronicle is a program of the Homeless Alliance, a non-profit in Oklahoma City providing income, housing, and employment opportunities for folks experiencing and at risk of homelessness. Thank you so much to editor @nathanpoppe! 
(Art = linocut with digital color)

#lino #printmaking #linocut #printmaker #reliefprint #blockprint #magazineillustration

Heeeey I’m teaching a hand-printing workshop at @flashfloodprint this Saturday, Sep 16, 10am-12pm! The link to register is in my profile. We’re going to hand-print some mini blocks of mine (you can take the prints home with you!) and you can also bring your own small block to print! Be sure to check out the other upcoming Printer Jam workshops: Collagraph with Katherine Hair Eagle (@katherinehair) on Sept 16; Cyanotype prints with Rachel Rector (@thereisnothere) on Sept 17; Paper weaving with Sarah Sullivan Sherrod (@sullysherrod) on Sept 23; Risograph zines with Ricardo Sanchez (@bekartoe) on Sept 23. Geometric letterpress with Jesse Warne (@circlogic) was this past weekend—go look at their work too! 

Printer Jam is a two-day celebration of all things printmaking, happening Friday Sept 22-Saturday Sept 23. Go to flashfloodprint.com/printer-jam to see the full list of festivities! I’ll see you there!
